ooks?id=EuouAQAAIAAJ|year=2001|last =Michelin|publisher=Michelin Travel Publications|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last= Messier|first=Ronald A.|title=The Almoravids and the Meanings of Jihad|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5YouJtx-igIC&pg=PA180|year=2010|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-38589-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Nanjira|first=Daniel Don|title=African Foreign Policy and Diplomacy From Antiquity to the 21st Century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LZuxGsXVPoMC&pg=PA208|year=2010|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-37982-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Naylor|first=Phillip C.|title=North Africa: A History from Antiquity to the Present|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a1jfzkJTAZgC&pg=PA90|year=2009|publisher=University of Texas Press|isbn=978-0-292-71922-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Pons|first1=Pau Obrador|last2=Crang|first2=Mike|last3=Travlou|first3=Penny|title=Cultures of Mass Tourism: Doing the Mediterranean in the Age of Banal Mobilities|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xqg0qJScQLUC&pg=PA39|year=2009|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-0-7546-7213-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Ring|first1=Trudy|last2=Salkin|first2=Robert M.|last3=Boda|first3=Sharon La|title=International Dictionary of Historic Places: Middle East and Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R44VRnNCzAYC&pg=PA468|year=1996|publisher=Fitzroy Dearborn Publishers|isbn=978-1-884964-03-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=[[Barnaby Rogerson|Rogerson]]|first1=[[Barnaby Rogerson|Barnaby]]|last2=Lavington|first2=Stephen|title=Marrakech: The Red City|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j-sPAQAAMAAJ|year=2004|publisher=Sickle Moon|isbn=978-1-900209-18-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Rogerson|first=Barnaby|title=Marrakesh, Fez, Rabat|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BK0neG2HIP4C&pg=PA106|year=2000|publisher=New Holland Publishers|isbn=978-1-86011-973-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Searight|first=Susan|title=Maverick Guide to Morocco|url=https://archive.