 Mountains Look on Marrakech|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dktmAAAACAAJ|year=2007|publisher=Whittles|isbn=978-1-870325-29-5}}\n* {{cite book|last=Canetti|first=Elias|title=The Voices of Marrakesh: A Record of a Visit|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RYySO-twrzwC|year=2012|publisher=Penguin Books Limited|isbn=978-0-14-119562-9}}\n* {{cite book|last=Charvet|first=Marie|title=Marrakesh|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dPrEGwAACAAJ|year=2003|publisher=Everyman|isbn=978-1-84159-073-8}}\n* {{cite book|last=Christiani|first=Kerry|title=Frommer's Marrakech Day by Day|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rvrf_AMIoMIC&pg=PA1|year=2010|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-470-71711-0}}\n* {{cite book|author=Editors of Time Out|title=Time Out Shortlist Marrakech|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JRDoGgAACAAJ|year=2008|publisher=Time Out|isbn=978-1-84670-076-7}}\n* {{cite book|last=Fernea|first=Elizabeth Warnock|title=A Street in Marrakech: A Personal View of Urban Women in Morocco|url=https://archive.org/details/streetinmarrakec00eliz|url-access=registration|year=1988|publisher=Waveland Press|isbn=978-0-88133-404-3}}\n* {{cite book|last=Gottreich|first=Emily|title=The Mellah of Marrakesh: Jewish And Muslim Space in Morocco's Red City|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c6fALw8d9ZoC&pg=PA10|year=2007|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-21863-6}}\n* {{cite book|last=Gould|first=Stephen Jay|title=The Lying Stones of Marrakech: Penultimate Reflections in Natural History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wApMpVmi-5gC|year=2011|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-06167-5}}\n* {{cite book|last=Humphreys|first=Andrew|title=Marrakech|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MdztGgAACAAJ|year=2008|publisher=Dorling Kindersley|isbn=978-1-4053-2827-2}}\n* {{cite book|last=Humphreys|first=Andrew|title=DK Eyewitness Top 10 Travel Guide: Marrakech: Marrakech|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Fwbcvk-rkLgC|year=2010|publisher=Dorling K