{"title_page": "List of diplomatic missions in Afghanistan", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Diplomatic missions in Afghanistan.PNG|thumb|right|400px|Map of diplomatic missions in Afghanistan]]\nThis is a '''list of diplomatic missions in [[Afghanistan]]'''. At present, the capital city of [[Kabul]] hosts 34 embassies.  With the presence of [[North Atlantic Treaty Organization|NATO]] troops, many of the organization's members have opened embassies in the country.  This listing excludes honorary consulates.\n\n== Embassies ==\nEmbassies in [[Kabul]]:\n[[File:Embassy of Russia in Kabul.jpg|thumb|[[Embassy of Russia in Kabul]]]]\n{{Location map many | Afghanistan\n                \n| width = 260   \n| float = right \n| border =\t\n| caption =\tLocations of Consulates in red\n               \n\n| label         = [[Kabul]]\n  | label1      =\n  | label1_size = 150 \n  | position    = left\n  | background  = \n  | mark1       = Blue pog.svg\n  | mark1size   = \n  | link1       = \n  | lat_deg     = 34.32 \n  | lon_deg     = 69.10\n\n| label2        = [[Herat]]\n  | label2_size = 100\n  | pos2        = bottom\n  | link2       = \n  | lat2_deg    = 34.2031 \n  | lon2_deg    = 62.1211\n\n| label3        = [[Jalalabad]]\n  | label3_size = 100\n  | pos3        = right\n  | link3       = \n  | lat3_deg    = 34.2603\n  | lon3_deg    = 70.2652\n\n| label4        = [[Kandahar]]\n  | pos4        = top\n  | link4       = \n  | lat4_deg    = 31.37\n  | lon4_deg    = 65.43\n\n| label5      = [[Mazar-e-Sharif]]\n  | pos5        = right\n  | link5       = \n  | lat5_deg    = 36.42\n  | lon5_deg    = 67.07\n\n}}\n\n{| \n|\n*{{AUS}} \n*{{BUL}}\n*{{CAN}} \n*{{CHN}} \n*{{CZE}}\n*{{DEN}}\n*{{EGY}}\n*{{FIN}} \n*{{FRA}} \n*{{GER}} \n*{{IND}}\n*{{INA}}\n*{{IRI}}\n*{{IRQ}}\n*{{ITA}}\n*{{JPN}} \n*{{KAZ}}\n*{{KGZ}}\n|valign=top|\n*{{NED}}\n*{{NOR}}\n*{{QAT}}\n*{{PAK}}\n*{{ROM}}\n*{{RUS}} \n*{{KSA}} \n*{{ROK}} \n*{{ESP}}\n*{{SWE}} \n*{{TJK}}\n*{{TUR}}\n*{{TKM}}\n*{