{"title_page": "Kyle Wright (baseball)", "text_new": "{{short description|American baseball player}}\n{{Infobox baseball biography\n|name        = Kyle Wright\n|image       = Kyle Wright (43445832524) (cropped).jpg\n|image_size  = 260\n|caption     = Wright with the [[Gwinnett Stripers]] in 2018\n|team        = Atlanta Braves\n|number      = 30\n|position    = [[Pitcher]]\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1995|10|2}}\n|birth_place = [[Huntsville, Alabama]] \n|bats        = Right\n|throws      = Right\n|debutleague = MLB\n|debutdate   = September 4\n|debutyear   = 2018\n|debutteam   = Atlanta Braves\n|statyear    = September 21, 2019\n|statleague = MLB\n|stat1label  = [[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n|stat1value  = 0-3\n|stat2label  = [[Earned run average]]\n|stat2value  = 7.71\n|stat3label  = [[Strikeout]]s\n|stat3value  = 23\n|teams       =\n* [[Atlanta Braves]] ({{mlby|2018}}\u2013present)\n}}\n'''Kyle Hardy Wright''' (born October 2, 1995) is an American [[professional baseball]] [[pitcher]] for the [[Atlanta Braves]] of [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB).\n\n==Early life==\nKyle was born in [[Huntsville, Alabama]], on October 2, 1995, to parents Roger and Belinda Wright. He has an elder brother, Mitchell, and younger brother Trey.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sapakoff |first1=Gene |title=Sapakoff: Vandy\u2019s projected No. 1 overall pick had the Wright stuff early on |url=https://www.postandcourier.com/columnists/sapakoff-vandy-s-projected-no-overall-pick-had-the-wright/article_036753c0-47ec-11e7-ac8e-7b28724ec88a.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Post and Courier |date=June 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sparks |first1=Adam |title=Vanderbilt's Kyle Wright, family face Super Regional game, draft in 48 hours |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2017/06/10/vanderbilts-kyle-wright-family-face-super-regional-game-draft-48-hours/384063001/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=USA Today |date=June 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Amateur career==\nWright attended [[Buckhorn High School (Alabama)|Buckhorn High School]] in [[New Market, Alabama]]. As a junior, he went 6\u20132 with a 0.88 [[earned run average]] (ERA) and 75 [[strikeouts]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Boyette|first=Daniel|date=April 6, 2015|accessdate=July 30, 2018|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2015/04/buckhorns_kyle_wright_named_se.html|title=Buckhorn's Kyle Wright named SEC baseball co-Freshman of the Week|work=The Birmingham News}}</ref> He committed to [[Vanderbilt University]] to play college baseball.<ref>{{cite news|work=The Birmingham News|first1=Daniel|last1=Boyette|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2013/04/buckhorn_pitcher_kyle_wright_c.html|title=Buckhorn pitcher Kyle Wright commits to Vanderbilt|date=April 12, 2013|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAs a freshman at Vanderbilt in 2015, Wright appeared in 29 games with three starts and went 6\u20131 with a 1.23 ERA, 62 strikeouts and four saves.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/vanderbilt-athletics/blog/20491946/vanderbilts-wright-patiently-prepped-for-sec-play|title=Vanderbilt's Wright patiently prepped for SEC play|work=Nashville Post|date=March 18, 2016|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2015/06/22/injured-hayden-stone-aids-vandy-reliever-kyle-wright-cws-debut/29113161/|title=Injured Hayden Stone aids Vandy's Kyle Wright in CWS|work=The Tennessean|first1=Adam|last1=Sparks|date=June 22, 2015|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/sports-business/blog/20484138/another-freshman-pitcher-thrives-for-vanderbilt-at-tournament-time|title=Another freshman pitcher thrives for Vanderbilt at tournament time|work=Nashville Post|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref> Wright became a full-time starter in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/vanderbilt-athletics/blog/20780361/vanderbilt-leads-sec-in-top-pitching-performances|title=Vanderbilt leads SEC in top pitching performances|work=Nashville Post}}</ref> In 16 starts, he went 8\u20134 with a 3.09 ERA and 107 strikeouts.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vanderbilt's Kyle Wright, Jeren Kendall are preseason All-Americans |url=http://sports.usatoday.com/2016/12/19/vanderbilts-kyle-wright-jeren-kendall-are-preseason-allamericans/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=USA Today |date=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Boyette |first1=Daniel |title=See the state players who are among Baseball America's top-100 draft prospects |url=https://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/03/see_the_state_players_who_are.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Birmingham News |date=March 23, 2017}}</ref> After the season, he played for the [[United States national baseball team|United States collegiate national team]].<ref>{{cite news|publisher=WZDX|url=https://www.rocketcitynow.com/sports/kye-wright-named-to-the-usa-baseball-collegiate-national-team/497465613|title=Kye Wright Named to the USA Baseball Collegiate National Team|accessdate=July 30, 2018|date=July 3, 2016|first1=Mo|last1=Carter}}</ref> As a junior in 2017, Wright went 5\u20136 with a 3.40 ERA and 121 strikeouts.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/06/kyle_wright_mlb_draft.html|title=Alabamian Kyle Wright drafted No. 5 overall by the Atlanta Braves|work=The Birmingham News|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=July 30, 2018|last1=Boyette|first1=Daniel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pouncy |first1=Colton |title=Former Vanderbilt pitcher Kyle Wright signs with Braves |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2017/06/16/vanderbilt/405324001/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Tennessean |date=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n===Atlanta Braves===\nThe [[Atlanta Braves]] selected Wright with the fifth overall selection of the [[2017 Major League Baseball draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/235998122/braves-draft-kyle-wright-from-vanderbilt-at-5/?topicId=27118140|title=Braves draft Kyle Wright from Vanderbilt at 5|publisher=MLB.com|first1=Mark|last1=Bowman|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref> He signed for a $7 million bonus on June 16 and was assigned to the [[GCL Braves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/236786138/braves-kyle-wright-agree-to-deal/|title=Braves, No. 5 pick Wright agree to deal|last=Bowman|first=Mark|publisher=MLB.com|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Wright was promoted to the [[Florida Fire Frogs]] in August 2017,<ref>{{cite news|title=Kyle Wright Added to Florida's Roster|url=https://www.milb.com/fire-frogs/news/kyle-wright-added-to-floridas-roster/c-245760266|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MILB.com|date=August 1, 2017}}</ref> and he finished the season there.<ref>{{cite news|title=Florida Drops Series Against Daytona With 4-3 Loss|url=https://www.milb.com/fire-frogs/news/florida-drops-series-against-daytona-with-4-3-loss/c-251923726|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MILB.com|date=September 1, 2017}}</ref> In nine games started between the two teams, he was 0\u20131 with a 2.65 ERA.<ref name=\"msstart\"/>\n\nWright received an invitation to spring training at the start of the 2018 season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bowman|first1=Mark|title=Wright excels in first taste of big league camp|url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/kyle-wright-impressive-in-first-braves-camp/c-267811860|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MLB.com|date=March 4, 2018}}</ref> He began the season with the [[Mississippi Braves]].<ref name=\"msstart\">{{cite news |last1=Boyette |first1=Daniel |title=Braves top pick, former Alabama HS ace Kyle Wright makes Double-A debut |url=https://www.al.com/sports/2018/04/braves_top_pick_former_alabama.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Birmingham News |date=April 6, 2018}}</ref> Wright pitched {{frac|109|1|3}} innings and recorded a 3.70 ERA alongside 105 strikeouts and 43 walks.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Carter |first1=Mo |title=Buckhorn graduate Kyle Wright is being promoted to Triple-A |url=https://www.rocketcitynow.com/sports/buckhorn-graduate-kyle-wright-is-being-promoted-to-triple-a/1335515432 |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |publisher=WZDX |date=July 30, 2018}}</ref> On July 30, 2018, Wright was promoted to the [[Gwinnett Stripers]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Roundup: Braves promote Wright, Allard |url=https://www.milb.com/milb/news/roundup-braves-promote-wright-allard/c-288060660 |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |publisher=MILB.com |date=July 30, 2018}}</ref> He faced the [[Norfolk Tides]] on August 3 in his [[International League]] debut.<ref>{{cite news |title=Top prospect Wright, two teammates flirt with no-hitter in Stripers win |url=https://www.gwinnettdailypost.com/sports/top-prospect-wright-two-teammates-flirt-with-no-hitter-in/article_0bcb7c2c-979a-11e8-a2a8-ab2cd2a62b08.html |accessdate=August 4, 2018 |work=Gwinnett Daily Post |date=August 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Battifarano |first1=Andrew |title=Wright shines in debut for Stripers |url=https://www.milb.com/milb/news/atlanta-braves-kyle-wright-produces-hitless-triple-a-debut/c-288752300 |accessdate=August 4, 2018 |publisher=MILB.com |date=August 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWright was called up to the major leagues for the first time on September 1, 2018. He was the first player from the 2017 draft class to make it to the majors.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Weinrib |first1=Ben |title=Wright, No. 2 prospect, among Braves' callups |url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/prospect-kyle-wright-joins-braves/c-292914464 |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |publisher=MLB.com |date=September 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Burns |first1=Gabriel |title=Kyle Wright joins Braves bullpen for playoff push |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/baseball/kyle-wright-joins-braves-bullpen-for-playoff-push/iaWCKJzEsIVcSMsv76VovM/ |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |work=Atlanta Journal Constitution |date=September 1, 2018}}</ref>  He made his major league debut on September 4 against the [[Boston Red Sox]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Odum |first1=Charles |title=Pearce drives in 3 runs as Red Sox beat Braves again, 5-1 |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/09/04/pearce-drives-in-3-runs-as-red-sox-beat-braves-again-5-1 |accessdate=April 14, 2019 |agency=Associated Press |via=Boston.com |publisher=Fox Sports |date=September 5, 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.foxsports.com/mlb/story/pearce-drives-in-3-runs-as-red-sox-beat-braves-again-5-1-090518 |archivedate=September 5, 2018}}</ref> Wright made the Braves' starting rotation at the start of the 2019 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Braves to have two rookie starters in rotation |url=http://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/26348631/braves-two-rookie-starters-rotation |accessdate=April 14, 2019 |publisher=ESPN.com |date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> He struggled through three starts, and was optioned to Gwinnett on April 13.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burns |first1=Gabriel |title=Kyle Wright struggles with strikes in Braves\u2019 loss to Mets |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/baseball/kyle-wright-struggles-with-strikes-braves-loss-mets/wTREpa35NeQc32KTReXSpO/ |accessdate=April 13, 2019 |work=Atlanta Journal Constitution |date=April 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bowman |first1=Mark |title=Braves option Wright, ready for Folty's return |url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/braves-option-prospect-kyle-wright-to-triple-a |accessdate=April 13, 2019 |publisher=MLB.com |date=April 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n{{baseballstats|mlb=657140|espn=39652|br=w/wrighky01|fangraphs=19665|brm=wright003kyl}}\n*[http://www.vucommodores.com/sports/m-basebl/mtt/kyle_wright_923559.html Vanderbilt Commodores bio]\n\n{{2017 MLB Draft}}\n{{Atlanta Braves first-round draft picks}}\n{{Atlanta Braves roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wright, Kyle}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Huntsville, Alabama]]\n[[Category:Baseball players from Alabama]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball pitchers]]\n[[Category:Atlanta Braves players]]\n[[Category:Vanderbilt Commodores baseball players]]\n[[Category:Gulf Coast Braves players]]\n[[Category:Florida Fire Frogs players]]\n[[Category:Mississippi Braves players]]\n[[Category:Gwinnett Stripers players]]\n[[Category:All-Star Futures Game players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American baseball player}}\n{{Infobox baseball biography\n|name        = Kyle Wright\n|image       = Kyle Wright (43445832524) (cropped).jpg\n|image_size  = 260\n|caption     = Wright with the [[Gwinnett Stripers]] in 2018\n|team        = Atlanta Braves\n|number      = 30\n|position    = [[Pitcher]]\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1995|10|2}}\n|birth_place = [[Huntsville, Alabama]] \n|bats        = Right\n|throws      = Right\n|debutleague = MLB\n|debutdate   = September 4\n|debutyear   = 2018\n|debutteam   = Atlanta Braves\n|statyear    = September 21, 2019\n|statleague = MLB\n|stat1label  = [[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n|stat1value  = 0-3\n|stat2label  = [[Earned run average]]\n|stat2value  = 7.71\n|stat3label  = [[Strikeout]]s\n|stat3value  = 23\n|teams       =\n* [[Atlanta Braves]] ({{mlby|2018}}\u2013present)\n}}\n'''Kyle Hardy Wright''' (born October 2, 1995) is an American [[professional baseball]] [[pitcher]] for the [[Atlanta Braves]] of [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB).\n\n==Early life==\nKyle was born in [[Huntsville, Alabama]], on October 2, 1995, to parents Roger and Belinda Wright. He has an elder brother, Mitchell, and younger brother Trey.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sapakoff |first1=Gene |title=Sapakoff: Vandy\u2019s projected No. 1 overall pick had the Wright stuff early on |url=https://www.postandcourier.com/columnists/sapakoff-vandy-s-projected-no-overall-pick-had-the-wright/article_036753c0-47ec-11e7-ac8e-7b28724ec88a.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Post and Courier |date=June 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sparks |first1=Adam |title=Vanderbilt's Kyle Wright, family face Super Regional game, draft in 48 hours |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2017/06/10/vanderbilts-kyle-wright-family-face-super-regional-game-draft-48-hours/384063001/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=USA Today |date=June 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Amateur career==\nWright attended [[Buckhorn High School (Alabama)|Buckhorn High School]] in [[New Market, Alabama]]. As a junior, he went 6\u20132 with a 0.88 [[earned run average]] (ERA) and 75 [[strikeouts]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Boyette|first=Daniel|date=April 6, 2015|accessdate=July 30, 2018|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2015/04/buckhorns_kyle_wright_named_se.html|title=Buckhorn's Kyle Wright named SEC baseball co-Freshman of the Week|work=The Birmingham News}}</ref> He committed to [[Vanderbilt University]] to play college baseball.<ref>{{cite news|work=The Birmingham News|first1=Daniel|last1=Boyette|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2013/04/buckhorn_pitcher_kyle_wright_c.html|title=Buckhorn pitcher Kyle Wright commits to Vanderbilt|date=April 12, 2013|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAs a freshman at Vanderbilt in 2015, Wright appeared in 29 games with three starts and went 6\u20131 with a 1.23 ERA, 62 strikeouts and four saves.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/vanderbilt-athletics/blog/20491946/vanderbilts-wright-patiently-prepped-for-sec-play|title=Vanderbilt's Wright patiently prepped for SEC play|work=Nashville Post|date=March 18, 2016|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2015/06/22/injured-hayden-stone-aids-vandy-reliever-kyle-wright-cws-debut/29113161/|title=Injured Hayden Stone aids Vandy's Kyle Wright in CWS|work=The Tennesseean|first1=Adam|last1=Sparks|date=June 22, 2015|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/sports-business/blog/20484138/another-freshman-pitcher-thrives-for-vanderbilt-at-tournament-time|title=Another freshman pitcher thrives for Vanderbilt at tournament time|work=Nashville Post|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref> Wright became a full-time starter in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|first1=David|last1=Boclair|accessdate=July 30, 2018|url=http://www.nashvillepost.com/sports/vanderbilt-athletics/blog/20780361/vanderbilt-leads-sec-in-top-pitching-performances|title=Vanderbilt leads SEC in top pitching performances|work=Nashville Post}}</ref> In 16 starts, he went 8\u20134 with a 3.09 ERA and 107 strikeouts.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vanderbilt's Kyle Wright, Jeren Kendall are preseason All-Americans |url=http://sports.usatoday.com/2016/12/19/vanderbilts-kyle-wright-jeren-kendall-are-preseason-allamericans/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=USA Today |date=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Boyette |first1=Daniel |title=See the state players who are among Baseball America's top-100 draft prospects |url=https://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/03/see_the_state_players_who_are.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Birmingham News |date=March 23, 2017}}</ref> After the season, he played for the [[United States national baseball team|United States collegiate national team]].<ref>{{cite news|publisher=WZDX|url=https://www.rocketcitynow.com/sports/kye-wright-named-to-the-usa-baseball-collegiate-national-team/497465613|title=Kye Wright Named to the USA Baseball Collegiate National Team|accessdate=July 30, 2018|date=July 3, 2016|first1=Mo|last1=Carter}}</ref> As a junior in 2017, Wright went 5\u20136 with a 3.40 ERA and 121 strikeouts.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/06/kyle_wright_mlb_draft.html|title=Alabamian Kyle Wright drafted No. 5 overall by the Atlanta Braves|work=The Birmingham News|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=July 30, 2018|last1=Boyette|first1=Daniel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pouncy |first1=Colton |title=Former Vanderbilt pitcher Kyle Wright signs with Braves |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/college/vanderbilt/2017/06/16/vanderbilt/405324001/ |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Tennessean |date=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n===Atlanta Braves===\nThe [[Atlanta Braves]] selected Wright with the fifth overall selection of the [[2017 Major League Baseball draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/235998122/braves-draft-kyle-wright-from-vanderbilt-at-5/?topicId=27118140|title=Braves draft Kyle Wright from Vanderbilt at 5|publisher=MLB.com|first1=Mark|last1=Bowman|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref> He signed for a $7 million bonus on June 16 and was assigned to the [[GCL Braves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/236786138/braves-kyle-wright-agree-to-deal/|title=Braves, No. 5 pick Wright agree to deal|last=Bowman|first=Mark|publisher=MLB.com|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Wright was promoted to the [[Florida Fire Frogs]] in August 2017,<ref>{{cite news|title=Kyle Wright Added to Florida's Roster|url=https://www.milb.com/fire-frogs/news/kyle-wright-added-to-floridas-roster/c-245760266|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MILB.com|date=August 1, 2017}}</ref> and he finished the season there.<ref>{{cite news|title=Florida Drops Series Against Daytona With 4-3 Loss|url=https://www.milb.com/fire-frogs/news/florida-drops-series-against-daytona-with-4-3-loss/c-251923726|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MILB.com|date=September 1, 2017}}</ref> In nine games started between the two teams, he was 0\u20131 with a 2.65 ERA.<ref name=\"msstart\"/>\n\nWright received an invitation to spring training at the start of the 2018 season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bowman|first1=Mark|title=Wright excels in first taste of big league camp|url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/kyle-wright-impressive-in-first-braves-camp/c-267811860|accessdate=March 6, 2018|publisher=MLB.com|date=March 4, 2018}}</ref> He began the season with the [[Mississippi Braves]].<ref name=\"msstart\">{{cite news |last1=Boyette |first1=Daniel |title=Braves top pick, former Alabama HS ace Kyle Wright makes Double-A debut |url=https://www.al.com/sports/2018/04/braves_top_pick_former_alabama.html |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |work=The Birmingham News |date=April 6, 2018}}</ref> Wright pitched {{frac|109|1|3}} innings and recorded a 3.70 ERA alongside 105 strikeouts and 43 walks.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Carter |first1=Mo |title=Buckhorn graduate Kyle Wright is being promoted to Triple-A |url=https://www.rocketcitynow.com/sports/buckhorn-graduate-kyle-wright-is-being-promoted-to-triple-a/1335515432 |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |publisher=WZDX |date=July 30, 2018}}</ref> On July 30, 2018, Wright was promoted to the [[Gwinnett Stripers]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Roundup: Braves promote Wright, Allard |url=https://www.milb.com/milb/news/roundup-braves-promote-wright-allard/c-288060660 |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |publisher=MILB.com |date=July 30, 2018}}</ref> He faced the [[Norfolk Tides]] on August 3 in his [[International League]] debut.<ref>{{cite news |title=Top prospect Wright, two teammates flirt with no-hitter in Stripers win |url=https://www.gwinnettdailypost.com/sports/top-prospect-wright-two-teammates-flirt-with-no-hitter-in/article_0bcb7c2c-979a-11e8-a2a8-ab2cd2a62b08.html |accessdate=August 4, 2018 |work=Gwinnett Daily Post |date=August 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Battifarano |first1=Andrew |title=Wright shines in debut for Stripers |url=https://www.milb.com/milb/news/atlanta-braves-kyle-wright-produces-hitless-triple-a-debut/c-288752300 |accessdate=August 4, 2018 |publisher=MILB.com |date=August 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWright was called up to the major leagues for the first time on September 1, 2018. He was the first player from the 2017 draft class to make it to the majors.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Weinrib |first1=Ben |title=Wright, No. 2 prospect, among Braves' callups |url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/prospect-kyle-wright-joins-braves/c-292914464 |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |publisher=MLB.com |date=September 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Burns |first1=Gabriel |title=Kyle Wright joins Braves bullpen for playoff push |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/baseball/kyle-wright-joins-braves-bullpen-for-playoff-push/iaWCKJzEsIVcSMsv76VovM/ |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |work=Atlanta Journal Constitution |date=September 1, 2018}}</ref>  He made his major league debut on September 4 against the [[Boston Red Sox]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Odum |first1=Charles |title=Pearce drives in 3 runs as Red Sox beat Braves again, 5-1 |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/09/04/pearce-drives-in-3-runs-as-red-sox-beat-braves-again-5-1 |accessdate=April 14, 2019 |agency=Associated Press |via=Boston.com |publisher=Fox Sports |date=September 5, 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.foxsports.com/mlb/story/pearce-drives-in-3-runs-as-red-sox-beat-braves-again-5-1-090518 |archivedate=September 5, 2018}}</ref> Wright made the Braves' starting rotation at the start of the 2019 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Braves to have two rookie starters in rotation |url=http://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/26348631/braves-two-rookie-starters-rotation |accessdate=April 14, 2019 |publisher=ESPN.com |date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> He struggled through three starts, and was optioned to Gwinnett on April 13.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burns |first1=Gabriel |title=Kyle Wright struggles with strikes in Braves\u2019 loss to Mets |url=https://www.ajc.com/sports/baseball/kyle-wright-struggles-with-strikes-braves-loss-mets/wTREpa35NeQc32KTReXSpO/ |accessdate=April 13, 2019 |work=Atlanta Journal Constitution |date=April 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bowman |first1=Mark |title=Braves option Wright, ready for Folty's return |url=https://www.mlb.com/braves/news/braves-option-prospect-kyle-wright-to-triple-a |accessdate=April 13, 2019 |publisher=MLB.com |date=April 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n{{baseballstats|mlb=657140|espn=39652|br=w/wrighky01|fangraphs=19665|brm=wright003kyl}}\n*[http://www.vucommodores.com/sports/m-basebl/mtt/kyle_wright_923559.html Vanderbilt Commodores bio]\n\n{{2017 MLB Draft}}\n{{Atlanta Braves first-round draft picks}}\n{{Atlanta Braves roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wright, Kyle}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Huntsville, Alabama]]\n[[Category:Baseball players from Alabama]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball pitchers]]\n[[Category:Atlanta Braves players]]\n[[Category:Vanderbilt Commodores baseball players]]\n[[Category:Gulf Coast Braves players]]\n[[Category:Florida Fire Frogs players]]\n[[Category:Mississippi Braves players]]\n[[Category:Gwinnett Stripers players]]\n[[Category:All-Star Futures Game players]]\n", "name_user": "Mandarax", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyle_Wright_(baseball)"}
{"title_page": "Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders", "text_new": "{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file = \n| painting_alignment = \n| image_size         = \n| title              = Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders\n| alt                = \n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      = \n| artist             = Jerome Meadows\n| year               = {{Start date|1997}}<ref name=\"DCComm\">{{cite web |title=Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders {{!}} Works {{!}} eMuseum {{!}} dcarts |url=http://dcarts.emuseum.com/objects/3233/carry-the-rainbow-on-your-shoulders?ctx=3d349f68-c592-4f8e-a4c7-b5977418fd9d&idx=0 |website=DC Commission on the Arts and Humanities |accessdate=7 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n| height_metric      = \n| width_metric       = \n| length_metric      = 243.84\n| height_imperial    = 304.8\n| width_imperial     = \n| length_imperial    = \n| metric_unit        = cm\n| imperial_unit      = in\n| city               = [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]\n| museum             = \n| coordinates        = {{Coord|38.923219|-77.041529|type:landmark_region:US-DC|display=title,inline}}\n| owner              = \n}}\n\n'''''Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders''''' is a public artwork by [[United States|American]] artist [[Jerome Meadows]], located in the [[Adams Morgan]] neighborhood in [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]. \"Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders\" was created through DC Commission on the Arts and Humanities.<ref name=\"NEA\">{{cite web | author=Liz Stark | year=2010 | title=Art Out Loud | publisher=National Endowment for the Arts | url=http://www.nea.gov/about/nearts/storyNew.php?id=07-outloud&issue=2010_v2 | accessdate=18 December 2010 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101217112905/http://nea.gov/about/NEARTS/storyNew.php?id=07-outloud&issue=2010_v2# | archive-date=2010-12-17 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n\nMade of a mix of concrete and mosaic the piece shows a faceless adult with a faceless child crawling on its back. The concrete sculptures are mixed with rainbow colored mosaic pieces. The sculpture sits in the center of Unity Park.\n\n==History of the piece==\n\nThe sculpture was chosen as site specific competition.<ref name=\"duck\">{{cite web | author=Jerome B. Meadows | year=1997 | title=Duck Season  | work= | publisher=Washington City Paper | url=http://www.washingtoncitypaper.com/articles/12252/duck-season | accessdate= 1 Feb 2011 }}</ref> \n\nIn May 2017, Unity Park underwent reconstruction and preservation work. ''Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders'' underwent conservation, including the fountain, which was restored to working order.<ref name=\"Goldchain\">{{cite web |last1=Goldchain |first1=Michelle |title=Adams Morgan\u2019s Unity Park will reopen on July 15 |url=https://dc.curbed.com/2017/7/13/15965014/adams-morgan-unity-park-reopen |website=Curbed DC |accessdate=7 January 2020 |language=en |date=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Jerome Meadows==\n\nMeadows was born in the [[Bronx, New York]] and received his B.F.A. in 1973 from the [[Rhode Island School of Design]] and his M.F.A. from the [[University of Maryland]] in 1981. As a previous faculty member at the [[Baltimore School for the Arts]], [[North Adams State College]] and the DC College of Fine Arts, Meadows settled in [[Savannah, Georgia]] in 1997. His work is seen in the collections of the cities of [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]], [[Alexandria, Virginia]] and [[Anchorage, Alaska]].<ref name=\"Snell\">{{cite web|year=2011 |title=Jerome Meadows |work=About The Gallery |publisher=Michele Snell Galleries, LLC |url=http://michelesnellgalleries.com/Jerome_Meadows.php |accessdate=1 Feb 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714084349/http://michelesnellgalleries.com/Jerome_Meadows.php |archivedate=2011-07-14 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/local/1997/03/06/in-new-park-a-monument-to-cooperation/81dc4c87-78b5-458f-9a10-8d38c1268583/ \"In New Park A Monument to Cooperation\"] from ''The Washington Post''\n\n{{Public art in Washington, D.C.|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Outdoor sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:1997 sculptures]]\n[[Category:Concrete sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Adams Morgan]]\n[[Category:Mosaic]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Washington, D.C.]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file = \n| painting_alignment = \n| image_size         = \n| title              = Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders\n| alt                = \n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      = \n| artist             = Jerome Meadows\n| year               = {{Start date|1997}}<ref name=\"DCComm\">{{cite web |title=Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders {{!}} Works {{!}} eMuseum {{!}} dcarts |url=http://dcarts.emuseum.com/objects/3233/carry-the-rainbow-on-your-shoulders?ctx=3d349f68-c592-4f8e-a4c7-b5977418fd9d&idx=0 |website=DC Commission on the Arts and Humanities |accessdate=7 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n| height_metric      = \n| width_metric       = \n| length_metric      = 243.84\n| height_imperial    = 304.8\n| width_imperial     = \n| length_imperial    = \n| metric_unit        = cm\n| imperial_unit      = in\n| city               = [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]\n| museum             = \n| coordinates        = {{Coord|38.923219|-77.041529|type:landmark_region:US-DC|display=title,inline}}\n| owner              = \n}}\n\n'''''Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders''''' is a public artwork by [[United States|American]] artist [[Jerome Meadows]], located in the [[Adams Morgan]] neighborhood in [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]]. \"Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders\" was created through DC Commission on the Arts and Humanities.<ref name=\"NEA\">{{cite web | author=Liz Stark | year=2010 | title=Art Out Loud | publisher=National Endowment for the Arts | url=http://www.nea.gov/about/nearts/storyNew.php?id=07-outloud&issue=2010_v2 | accessdate=18 December 2010 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101217112905/http://nea.gov/about/NEARTS/storyNew.php?id=07-outloud&issue=2010_v2# | archive-date=2010-12-17 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n\nMade of a mix of concrete and mosaic the piece shows a faceless adult with a faceless child crawling on its back. The concrete sculptures are mixed with rainbow colored mosaic pieces. The sculpture sits in the center of Unity Park.\n\n==History of the piece==\n\nThe sculpture was chosen as site specific competition.<ref name=\"duck\">{{cite web | author=Jerome B. Meadows | year=1997 | title=Duck Season  | work= | publisher=Washington City Paper | url=http://www.washingtoncitypaper.com/articles/12252/duck-season | accessdate= 1 Feb 2011 }}</ref> \n\nIn May 2017, Unity Park underwent reconstruction and preservation work. ''Carry the Rainbow on Your Shoulders'' underwent conservation, including the fountain, which was restored to working order.<ref name=\"Goldchain\">{{cite web |last1=Goldchain |first1=Michelle |title=Adams Morgan\u2019s Unity Park will reopen on July 15 |url=https://dc.curbed.com/2017/7/13/15965014/adams-morgan-unity-park-reopen |website=Curbed DC |accessdate=7 January 2020 |language=en |date=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Jerome Meadows==\n\nMeadows was born in the [[Bronx, New York]] and received his B.F.A. in 1973 from the [[Rhode Island School of Design]] and his M.F.A. from the [[University of Maryland]] in 1981. As a previous faculty member at the [[Baltimore School for the Arts]], [[North Adams State College]] and the DC College of Fine Arts, Meadows settled in [[Savannah, Georgia]] in 1997. His work is seen in the collections of the cities of [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]], [[Alexandria, Virginia]] and [[Anchorage, Alaska]].<ref name=\"Snell\">{{cite web|year=2011 |title=Jerome Meadows |work=About The Gallery |publisher=Michele Snell Galleries, LLC |url=http://michelesnellgalleries.com/Jerome_Meadows.php |accessdate=1 Feb 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714084349/http://michelesnellgalleries.com/Jerome_Meadows.php |archivedate=2011-07-14 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/local/1997/03/06/in-new-park-a-monument-to-cooperation/81dc4c87-78b5-458f-9a10-8d38c1268583/ \"In New Park A Monument to Cooperation\"] from ''The Washington Post''\n\n[[Category:Outdoor sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:1997 sculptures]]\n[[Category:Concrete sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Adams Morgan]]\n[[Category:Mosaic]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Washington, D.C.]]\n", "name_user": "Ham II", "label": "safe", "comment": "+Template:Public art in Washington, D.C.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carry_the_Rainbow_on_Your_Shoulders"}
